'''管鬚蟹科'''（[[學名|學名]]：{{lang|la|'''Albuneidae'''}}）是[[十足目|十足目]] [[異尾下目|異尾下目]][[蟬蟹總科|蟬蟹總科]]之下的另一個科<ref name=frienews />，其物種與蟬蟹科的物種關係密切<ref name="Davie">{{cite book |1= |author=P. J. F. Davie |year=2002 |title=Crustacea: Malocostraca: Eucarida (Part 2), Decapoda: Anomura, Brachyura |series=Volume 19 of Zoological catalogue of Australia, Australia |isbn=978-0-643-05677-0 |publisher=[[CSIRO_Publishing|CSIRO Publishing]] |chapter=Hippidae |pages=68–70 |url=http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=jr9SR1Cr5BAC&pg=PA68 |access-date=2014-08-22 |archive-date=2014-08-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140826115357/http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=jr9SR1Cr5BAC&pg=PA68 |dead-url=no }}</ref> 。

與[[蟬蟹科|蟬蟹科]]物種一樣，本科物種亦常埋藏在沙裡<ref name=frienews>{{cite journal |url=http://www.tfrin.gov.tw/friweb/frienews/enews0050/s1.html |title=潛沙高手——蟬蟹 |journal=水試所電子報 |publisher=行政院農業委員會水產試驗所 |issue=50 |year=2010 |date=2010-06-29 |language=zh-hant |access-date=2014-08-22 |archive-date=2019-09-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190917214451/http://www.tfrin.gov.tw/friweb/frienews/enews0050/s1.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。但其獨特像長管一樣的觸角成為了分辨兩個科物種的標誌。除此之後，外界對其認識依然不太深。

==分類==
本科有十個屬，合共約50個物種，當中還包括9個化石物種<ref name="Grave"/>；已描述的化石種樣本來自[[白堊紀|白堊紀]]<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://www.city.mizunami.gifu.jp/odocs/sightseeing/mizunami/cultural_property/institution/Bull29/BMFM29-069-072%28116kB%29.pdf |journal=[[Bulletin_of_the_Mizunami_Fossil_Museum|Bulletin of the Mizunami Fossil Museum]] |volume=29 |year=2002 |pages=69–72 |title=The first record of albuneid crabs (Crustacea, Decapoda) from the Cretaceous |author=René H. B. Fraaije |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110612184536/http://www.city.mizunami.gifu.jp/odocs/sightseeing/mizunami/cultural_property/institution/Bull29/BMFM29-069-072(116kB).pdf |archivedate=2011-06-12 }}</ref>、[[中新世|中新世]]<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://www.city.mizunami.gifu.jp/odocs/sightseeing/mizunami/cultural_property/institution/Bull34/02.pdf |journal=[[Bulletin_of_the_Mizunami_Fossil_Museum|Bulletin of the Mizunami Fossil Museum]] |volume=34 |year=2008 |title=''Albunea turritellacola'', a new sand crab (Anomura, Albuneidae) from the lower Miocene of southwest France |pages=17–22 |author=René H. B. Fraaije, Barry W. M. van Bakel & John W. M. Jagt |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110612184554/http://www.city.mizunami.gifu.jp/odocs/sightseeing/mizunami/cultural_property/institution/Bull34/02.pdf |archivedate=2011-06-12 }}</ref>及[[漸新世|漸新世]]<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://decapoda.nhm.org/pdfs/30376/30376.pdf |title=A new genus of fossil sand crab (Anomura: Albuneidae) from the Oligocene of Italy |author=Christopher B. Boyko |journal=[[Palaeontology_(journal)|Palaeontology]] |volume=47 |issue=4 |year=2004 |pages=933–936 |doi=10.1111/j.0031-0239.2004.00391.x |access-date=2014-08-22 |archive-date=2016-03-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303171500/http://decapoda.nhm.org/pdfs/30376/30376.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。
